FAQs
Is the medical degree from Serbia recognized internationally?

Yes, medical degrees from Serbian universities are recognized by major medical councils and organizations worldwide.

What is the language of instruction for medical programs in Serbia?
Many medical programs in Serbia are taught in English, making them accessible to international students.

How much does it cost to study medicine in Serbia?

Tuition fees for medical programs in Serbia range from €5,000 to €8,000 per year, with living expenses averaging €400 to €700 per month.

Are there scholarships available for international students in Serbia?

Yes, various scholarships are available from universities and government organizations based on academic merit and financial need.

